remarks.format:


## Remarks  
 The extended form of a distinguished name includes a string representation of the objectGUID property of an object. For security principal objects such as users, groups, and computers, the extended form also includes a string representation of the objectSID property. For more information about the objectGUID and objectSID properties, see [Object-Guid](/windows/desktop/adschema/a-objectguid) and [Object-Sid](/windows/desktop/adschema/a-objectsid).



## Examples  
 The following C# example shows how to return a collection of distinguished names in hexadecimal format.  

```csharp  
using System.DirectoryServices;  
...  
DirectorySearcher src = new DirectorySearcher("…");  
src.PropertiesToLoad = new string[] {ntSecurityDescriptor,…};  
src.ExtendedDN = ExtendedDN.HexString;  
SearchResultCollection res = src.FindAll();  

```
